<span id="freeTextContainer7079634432930324522">3.5 Stars from me<br/><br/>I love New York and having stood beside the NYPD office in Times Square the setting for this story really resonated with me.<br/><br/>Median Gray is an old timey 1980s traditional cop thriller and it featured some fascinating insights into policing procedures that I know a lot of people will find captivating.<br/><br/>It&apos;s a slow burn, bear with the scene setting and character introductions and hold on for the main thrust of the story to kick in - it&apos;s worth it. The characters are well defined and </span>
  <span id="freeText7079634432930324522" style="display:none">3.5 Stars from me<br /><br />I love New York and having stood beside the NYPD office in Times Square the setting for this story really resonated with me.<br /><br />Median Gray is an old timey 1980s traditional cop thriller and it featured some fascinating insights into policing procedures that I know a lot of people will find captivating.<br /><br />It's a slow burn, bear with the scene setting and character introductions and hold on for the main thrust of the story to kick in - it's worth it. The characters are well defined and I could almost smell the streets of NYC.</span>
