        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3768206868" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer31982925758403143">I received this book from the publisher for an honest review.<br/> The book takes place in New York City beginning in 1963 with a rookie beat cop. This was back when they still had them walking the beat as they say. Taking you through his first days and months on the job meeting the people, shop owners and then when trouble happens not having a radio but going to a call box calling in for assistance. Told to wait he does not.<br/> You are then taken through the rest of the story through time and different</span>
  <span id="freeText31982925758403143" style="display:none">I received this book from the publisher for an honest review.<br /> The book takes place in New York City beginning in 1963 with a rookie beat cop. This was back when they still had them walking the beat as they say. Taking you through his first days and months on the job meeting the people, shop owners and then when trouble happens not having a radio but going to a call box calling in for assistance. Told to wait he does not.<br /> You are then taken through the rest of the story through time and different characters that only add to the story. Along with the officers some waiting to make a difference and some dirty. The author gives you a look into the life of the ’80s and much of what it was like in New York and not the glitz side either. This is what makes this story tick along with the characters which only add to this story. This will keep you wanting you to turn to the next page until the end. A very good book. I received this book from Netgalley.com I gave it 4 stars. Follow us at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.1rad-readerreviews.com">www.1rad-readerreviews.com</a><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="31982925758403143" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


